    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-14T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="569"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d569">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to M. <persName
                            type="to">Thiébaut</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 14, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 344.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                    your note of the 8th instant relating to the readiness of this Government and of
                    that of Great Britain to submit to the arbitration of the King of Sweden <pb
                        facs="0573" n="475" xml:id="pg_475"/> and Norway the claims of French
                    citizens arising out of recent events in Samoa.</p>
                <p>The Department will await the reply of the German Government upon this question
                    which you have promised to communicate.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
